  "text": "Stem cells come from various sources, and although they share some common properties, they also differ in many respects and behave differently in terms of their rate of differentiation, trophic factor secretion, and their stimulation of endogenous processes when in a pathologic environment [CITATION_1] . The key source and type of stem cells of the selected studies were human (bone marrow) and mesenchymal. Although the study by Daadi et al. [CITATION_2] had a better behavior status, using neural embryonic stem cells, the majority of studies used MSCs (60%), some studies used neural stem cells (20%) or embryonic stem cells (20%), and no studies compared the different cell types in the same experiment ( Figure 3) .",
